<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1230,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1230,1255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Best distinguished by the R 
<number box="[594,602,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[611,618,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
fork distal to the position of the M 
<number box="[1020,1025,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1036,1045,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
fork, shorter than the length of R 
<number box="[1428,1436,1245,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,246,1269,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
); shape of the male cercus being incurved apically, longer than epandrium in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1378,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[1349,1378,1270,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) and phallus with two posterolateral pointed projections (
<figureCitation box="[735,819,1305,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[787,819,1306,1330]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1230,2025]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,794]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1341,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Description</emphasis>
. Male (
<figureCitation box="[435,524,1341,1366]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[493,524,1341,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,612,1341,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[480,494,1378,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face which bears fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[904,946,1414,1438]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
setulae; one pair of distinct vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate smaller postocular setae; occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[771,804,1521,1546]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[1119,1154,1522,1546]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1557,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[254,337,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[306,337,1557,1582]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; dorsum yellow, except brownish on mediotergite and median stripe on prothoracic collar; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number box="[403,417,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[568,624,1629,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[641,726,1629,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,726,1629,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[958,968,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[1000,1034,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.4">1.4</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[1426,1436,1630,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[247,282,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">6X</date>
as long as wide. F 
<number box="[500,510,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[542,575,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C1, 
<date box="[775,810,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">4X</date>
as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number box="[1207,1221,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number box="[1231,1302,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16–17</number>
/ 
<number box="[1312,1321,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1338,1409,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
/ 
<number box="[1419,1432,1665,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[460,498,1702,1726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number box="[510,524,1702,1726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, black, without distal discontinuity, converging distally but divergent at tip. T 
<number box="[249,259,1738,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[296,331,1737,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.6">0.6</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[510,521,1738,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number box="[1150,1164,1738,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number box="[1273,1343,1737,1762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; slight apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[321,331,1810,1834]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
bearing strong apical spine. Mid and hind legs slender with fine setae but T 
<number box="[1185,1197,1810,1834]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[409,474,1845,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[494,585,1845,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[553,585,1845,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane faintly yellow, veins yellowish; R 
<number box="[1144,1152,1860,1874]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1161,1168,1860,1874]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[689,774,1885,1909]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[1076,1084,1899,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[1157,1165,1899,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[1198,1206,1899,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1215,1222,1899,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
fork acute (~ 
<number box="[1380,1412,1884,1909]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number box="[409,414,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[424,433,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by shorter than R 
<number box="[699,707,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[742,750,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[834,842,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
diverging distally; vein R 
<number box="[1143,1151,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 
<date box="[1184,1218,1923,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
<number box="[1184,1198,1923,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="3.0">3</number>
X
</date>
as long as R 
<number box="[1371,1379,1938,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number box="[533,541,1976,1990]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<date box="[575,610,1962,1986]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">
<number box="[575,588,1962,1986]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1067,1184,1961,1986]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1198,1328,1961,1986]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="216">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number box="[151,165,2001,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[219,233,2001,2024]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellowish, tergites 
<number box="[635,677,2000,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
and 
<number box="[738,752,2001,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish with distinct setae on posterior margin; tergite 
<number box="[1400,1414,2001,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="216" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number box="[382,398,1901,1925]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[410,541,1900,1925]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brownish. Cercus narrow, curved up distally with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1423,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Figs 27, 28</figureCitation>
); left and right cerci closely approximated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[791,876,1937,1962]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number box="[844,876,1937,1961]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium wide, subrectangular in lateral view, with strong setae on outer face at apex (
<figureCitation box="[600,684,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number box="[652,684,1973,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[824,906,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,906,1973,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) bilobed, with spine-like setae on inner face of outer lobe. Hypandrium rather rounded in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[827,915,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
Fig. 
<number box="[885,915,2009,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
), not markedly inflated, with distinct setae; gonocoxal apodeme confined to anterior margin of hypandrium, lacking narrow process. Subepandrial sclerite concave on anterior margin, two short finger-like posterior processes with long setae at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1331,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
Fig. 
<number box="[1299,1331,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus sclerotized with two posterolateral pointed projections, extending well beyond hypandrium apex, apical membranous area covered with minute dark spicules (
<figureCitation box="[753,837,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 31" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1795]" captionTargetBox="[161,1434,193,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1434,193,1751]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 31. Hemerodromia collini sp. nov., 25, holotype ♂. 26 – 31, paratype ♂. holotype ♂. 25. habitus, lateral view; 26. wing. 27. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 28. terminalia, lateral view; 29. cercus, subepandrial sclerite and surstylus, dorsal view; 30. phallus, lateral view; 31. hypandrium, phallus and epandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252072/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
Fig. 
<number box="[805,837,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1185,1328,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Body length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[1343,1432,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[305,394,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[404,491,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
