<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="218" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,511,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is in tribute to J.E. Collin in recognition of his contribution to the knowledge of the Neotropical fauna of 
<taxonomicName box="[461,586,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Empididae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,794]" box="[199,1272,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Variations</emphasis>
. Body varying from 
<quantity box="[558,644,584,608]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[679,768,583,608]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Wing length varying from 
<quantity box="[1078,1143,584,608]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[1178,1267,583,608]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[325,577,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[325,577,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Hemerodromia collini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,681,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[588,681,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[842,988,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maturaca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[842,988,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">H. maturaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[998,1092,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[998,1092,620,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the R 
<number box="[1205,1213,635,649]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1222,1229,635,649]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="5.0">5</number>
fork distal to the position of the M 
<number box="[347,352,673,687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[362,371,673,687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="2.0">2</number>
fork, shorter than the length of R 
<number box="[750,759,673,687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="4.0">4</number>
; subepandrial sclerite with 
<number box="[1067,1081,659,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="2.0">2</number>
finger-like posterior processes; and epandrium subrectangular. 
<taxonomicName box="[514,765,697,721]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[514,765,697,721]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">Hemerodromia collini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[776,870,697,722]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[776,870,697,722]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the latter by the shape of the male cercus being incurved apically, and phallus with 
<number box="[705,719,734,758]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" value="2.0">2</number>
posterolateral pointed projections. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1294,734,757]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maturaca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1152,1294,734,757]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">H. maturaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1303,1393,733,758]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1303,1393,733,758]" pageId="9" pageNumber="218">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the cercus is almost straight apically and phallus have no posterolateral pointed projections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
